comments.body:
Just checked against the real deal:

- instances are using internal DNS only (ie, for our case, the dhcp server would give away the CLC IP address);
- the internal DNS is forwarding requests it doesn't know, which is a different behavior than what we are doing (ie 
{code}
graziano@x220t:~/.ec2/aws-eucalyptus$ nslookup www.google.com communitycloud.eucalyptus.com
Server:		communitycloud.eucalyptus.com
Address:	173.205.188.7#53

Non-authoritative answer:
*** Can't find www.google.com: No answer
{code}
- any DNS requests coming from an instance for a name of any other instance (either public or private) will return the private IP (ie, trying to resolve either the public name, or private name of an instance -- and it doesn't matter if they are in the same security group or not -- will return the private IP);
- a DNS request for the private name from outside the cloud, will fail;
- a DNS request for the public name from outside the cloud, will return the public IP.
